&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;At Go1, we’re on a mission to help organizations deliver learning and development in more relevant, timely, and effective ways.&lt;strong data-stringify-type=&quot;bold&quot;&gt;&lt;em data-stringify-type=&quot;italic&quot;&gt; &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;From a small startup to now a global brand - we’ve grown by solving hard problems, embracing ambiguity, and never standing still.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;If you thrive on change, get energy from big, complex challenges, and are excited to grow fast alongside smart, ambitious people, then Go1 might be exactly what you’re looking for. We offer autonomy with accountability, space to experiment, and the opportunity to shape solutions that impact millions of learners worldwide. We don’t have all the answers — and that’s the point. We figure it out together. Every line of code, every conversation, every bold idea helps move us closer to our mission:&amp;nbsp;to enable individuals, organizations, and society to progress. There’s still so much to build — and even more to discover. &lt;strong&gt;Go there with us...&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;We’re entering one of the most exciting chapters in Go1’s history. As we continue to bring new products to market, build AI-powered capabilities, and help organisations rethink workforce enablement, we’re looking for a commercially minded Customer Success Manager to help our customers get more value from Go1.&amp;nbsp;If you’re energised by building strong customer relationships, spotting growth opportunities, and owning outcomes across retention and expansion, this role was built for you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why you’ll love this role:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Go where the customer is going, not where they’ve been. You’ll work with mid-market customers as they navigate changing workforce needs, new products, and new ways of using learning technology.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Go beyond adoption. You’ll own the customer relationship across value, retention, renewal, and growth.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Go work with good humans. Kind, candid, globally connected, and genuinely invested in helping customers succeed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the role:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Go1, Customer Success is about helping customers get real business value from learning, while building long-term, commercially healthy partnerships.&amp;nbsp;We’re looking for a Customer Success Manager to own and grow a portfolio of mid-market customers across APAC. You’ll partner closely with Learning, HR, and People leaders to help them connect their workforce development goals to the value Go1 can deliver, from onboarding and adoption through to renewals, expansion, and strategic planning.This role would suit someone who enjoys the mix of relationship management, problem-solving, commercial ownership, and customer strategy. You’ll need to be comfortable working in a fast-moving remote environment, balancing competing priorities, building relationships across customer organisations, and taking ownership of outcomes, not just activity.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Customer Success and Retention&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own and grow a portfolio of mid-market customers, acting as their trusted strategic partner&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build strong, multi-threaded relationships across customer organisations, from day-to-day users through to executive decision-makers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead onboarding, adoption, business reviews, and success planning to help customers maximise the value of their Go1 partnership&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use customer insights, product usage, and business goals to identify risk, improve retention, and support successful renewals&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help customers understand and adopt new Go1 products and capabilities as we continue to innovate&

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;At Go1, we’re on a mission to help organizations deliver learning and development in more relevant, timely, and effective ways.&lt;strong data-stringify-type=&quot;bold&quot;&gt;&lt;em data-stringify-type=&quot;italic&quot;&gt; &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;From a small startup to now a global brand - we’ve grown by solving hard problems, embracing ambiguity, and never standing still.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;If you thrive on change, get energy from big, complex challenges, and are excited to grow fast alongside smart, ambitious people, then Go1 might be exactly what you’re looking for. We offer autonomy with accountability, space to experiment, and the opportunity to shape solutions that impact millions of learners worldwide. We don’t have all the answers — and that’s the point. We figure it out together. Every line of code, every conversation, every bold idea helps move us closer to our mission:&amp;nbsp;to enable individuals, organizations, and society to progress. There’s still so much to build — and even more to discover. &lt;strong&gt;Go there with us...&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a Director of Data Intelligence to lead the next phase of that ecosystem.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is not a dashboard-factory role. It is a chance to shape how a global SaaS business understands itself, makes decisions and turns data into customer and commercial advantage.You will report to the CTO, leading a multidisciplinary team across analytics, data engineering and data science. Your mandate is to make trusted data easier to use than local workarounds, give the business confidence in it&#39;s most critical metrics, and build the foundations for AI-assisted decision-making at scale.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;none&quot;&gt;What you&#39;ll own:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will set the direction for Data Intelligence at Go1, with a focus on trusted business metrics, governed self-service, reusable data products, and practical business impact.&amp;nbsp;You will help Go1 answer questions like:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Which metrics can we trust for company-level decisions?&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Where do ARR, retention, churn, product adoption, and customer health signals disagree, and why?&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;How do we make trusted data discoverable and usable by leaders, teams, and AI tools?&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;How do we help domains own their operating evidence without fragmenting company truth?&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Which data products will materially improve customer outcomes, commercial performance, or decision speed?&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you&#39;ll do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead Go1’s Data Intelligence strategy in partnership with the CTO, Product, Engineering, Finance, Customer, GTM, Legal, and Risk leaders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strengthen Go1’s trusted business spine: shared definitions, semantic layers, metric ownership, data quality, lineage, observability, metadata, and governance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Scale self-service analytics in a way that increases confidence rather than creating more unreconciled numbers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Turn data assets into reusable products that support customer health, churn prevention, product adoption, forecasting, planning, PLG, business reviews, and executive decision-making.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare Go1’s data ecosystem for AI-assisted analysis by making definitions, trust levels, ownership, and approved evidence paths machine-readable and human-usable.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build clarity around where Data Intelligence owns the foundation, where domains own operating evidence, and how weak or unsupported claims are challenged constructively.&lt;/li&gt;
